{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Collision, Physics & Scoring Validation",
  "description": "When index.html or any .js file is saved, validates collision boundary correctness, physics constant usage, and scoring logic integrity against the design spec.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": ["index.html", "*.js", "**/*.js"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A game file was just saved. Validate collision boundaries, physics constants, and scoring logic. Report only violations.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Collision Boundary Integrity\n\n**Hitbox construction**\n- Does ghostyHitbox() return exactly { x: ghosty.x + C.HITBOX_INSET, y: ghosty.y + C.HITBOX_INSET, w: C.GHOSTY_W - 2 * C.HITBOX_INSET, h: C.GHOSTY_H - 2 * C.HITBOX_INSET }? Any asymmetric inset makes near-misses feel unfair.\n- Is C.HITBOX_INSET applied on all four sides — not just top/left? Flag if width or height uses a single inset instead of 2 * C.HITBOX_INSET.\n- Is ghostyHitbox() a pure function with no side effects? It must not modify ghosty state.\n\n**Pipe boundary construction**\n- Is the top pipe boundary { x: pipe.x, y: 0, w: C.PIPE_WIDTH, h: pipe.gapY - C.PIPE_GAP / 2 }? Flag any deviation — especially if PIPE_GAP is not halved.\n- Is the bottom pipe boundary { x: pipe.x, y: pipe.gapY + C.PIPE_GAP / 2, w: C.PIPE_WIDTH, h: C.CANVAS_H }? The height must extend to C.CANVAS_H, not a fixed value.\n- Are pipe boundaries computed on the fly from the current pipe.x and pipe.gapY each frame, not cached from a previous frame?\n\n**AABB overlap test**\n- Does rectsOverlap(a, b) use strict less-than (<) on all four comparisons: a.x < b.x+b.w, a.x+a.w > b.x, a.y < b.y+b.h, a.y+a.h > b.y? Using <= on any side causes false positives when Ghosty grazes a pipe edge.\n- Is rectsOverlap a pure function — no canvas draws, no state mutations, no console.log in production?\n- Is rectsOverlap called with (hitbox, pipeRect) in that order consistently? Argument order doesn't affect AABB math but inconsistency signals a copy-paste error.\n\n**Ground and ceiling checks**\n- Is the ground check hb.y + hb.h >= C.CANVAS_H (bottom edge of hitbox reaches canvas bottom)? Using ghosty.y instead of hb.y misses the hitbox inset.\n- Is the ceiling check hb.y <= 0 (top edge of hitbox reaches canvas top)? Using ghosty.y - C.HITBOX_INSET would be off by the inset amount.\n- Are ground/ceiling checks evaluated before the pipe loop so the cheaper O(1) checks short-circuit first?\n- Does a ground/ceiling collision trigger the same triggerCollision() path as a pipe collision — not a separate code path that might skip screen shake or audio?\n\n**Invincibility guard**\n- Is `if (ghosty.invincible) return;` the very first line of checkCollisions()? Any collision logic before this guard could fire during the death flash.\n- After triggerCollision() sets ghosty.invincible = true, is checkCollisions() guaranteed to return early on the very next frame without re-triggering?\n\n---\n\n## 2. Physics Constants Integrity\n\n**No raw literals in physics code**\n- Are there any raw numeric literals in ghostyUpdate(), ghostyFlap(), pipesUpdate(), or currentPipeSpeed()? Every number must reference C.CONSTANT_NAME. Flag each raw literal with its value and the constant it should use.\n- Is C.GRAVITY a positive number (downward acceleration adds to vy which is positive-down)? A negative GRAVITY would invert physics.\n- Is C.ASCENT_VELOCITY a negative number (upward velocity is negative in canvas coordinates)? A positive value would make flap push Ghosty down.\n- Is C.TERMINAL_VELOCITY a positive number used as a max clamp (Math.min(vy, C.TERMINAL_VELOCITY))? Using Math.max would invert the clamp.\n\n**Physics operation order**\n- In ghostyUpdate(), does gravity apply before the terminal velocity clamp, which applies before position integration? The canonical order is: vy += GRAVITY*dt → vy = min(vy, TERMINAL_VELOCITY) → y += vy*dt. Any reordering changes the physics.\n- Is dt multiplied into gravity (C.GRAVITY * dt) and position (vy * dt) — never applied as a raw per-frame offset?\n- Is C.MAX_DELTA enforced before dt reaches any physics function — not inside individual update functions? Clamping inside each function means some paths could still receive an unclamped dt.\n\n**Pipe speed formula**\n- Does currentPipeSpeed() implement exactly: Math.min(C.PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL + Math.floor(score / C.PIPE_SPEED_THRESHOLD) * C.PIPE_SPEED_INCREMENT, C.PIPE_SPEED_MAX)?\n- Is Math.floor used (not Math.round or Math.ceil) for the threshold step count? Round/ceil would trigger speed increases before the threshold is fully reached.\n- Does currentPipeSpeed() read the live score variable, not a cached copy that could be stale?\n- At score 0, does currentPipeSpeed() return exactly C.PIPE_SPEED_INITIAL?\n- At score = C.PIPE_SPEED_THRESHOLD * N where N is large enough to exceed the cap, does currentPipeSpeed() return exactly C.PIPE_SPEED_MAX and no more?\n\n**Cloud parallax scaling**\n- Does cloudScrollSpeed(layer) compute currentPipeSpeed() * multiplier — not a cached pipe speed? Cloud speed must scale dynamically with difficulty.\n- Are the two layer multipliers C.CLOUD_SPEED_FAR and C.CLOUD_SPEED_NEAR (not hardcoded 0.3 / 0.7)?\n- Is layer 0 always slower than layer 1 (C.CLOUD_SPEED_FAR < C.CLOUD_SPEED_NEAR)? Swapping them inverts the parallax depth effect.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Scoring Logic Integrity\n\n**Score increment correctness**\n- Is score incremented by exactly 1 per pipe — not by a variable amount or by the number of active pipes?\n- Is the scoring condition based on Ghosty's centre passing the pipe's right edge: ghosty.x + C.GHOSTY_W / 2 > pipe.x + C.PIPE_WIDTH? Using ghosty.x alone scores too early; using ghosty.x + C.GHOSTY_W scores too late.\n- Is pipe.scored checked before incrementing (if (!pipe.scored)) and set to true immediately after? A missing flag allows the same pipe to score on every subsequent frame.\n- Is pipe.scored only reset in pipesReset() (on game restart) and spawnPipe() (on pool slot reuse) — never in pipesUpdate() during normal scrolling?\n\n**Score and difficulty sync**\n- Is currentPipeSpeed() called after score is incremented in the same frame, so the speed increase takes effect immediately on the threshold frame?\n- Does the score display read the live score variable, not a copy captured at frame start?\n- Is the high score comparison score > storageGetHighScore() (strict greater-than), so a tied score does not overwrite the stored value unnecessarily?\n- Is storageSetHighScore() called exactly once per game over — in enterState(State.GAME_OVER) — not on every frame of the GAME_OVER state render?\n\n**Score popup placement**\n- Is effectsSpawnPopup called with the pipe gap centre coordinates (pipe.x + C.PIPE_WIDTH / 2, pipe.gapY) — not Ghosty's position?\n- Is effectsSpawnPopup called exactly once per score increment — guarded by the same pipe.scored flag?\n- Does the popup age increment in effectsUpdate(dt) only when currentState === State.PLAYING, not during PAUSED?\n\n---\n\nOutput only violations with the function name, a one-line description of the problem, and a one-line fix. If all three domains are valid, output \"✅ Collision boundaries, physics constants, and scoring logic are all correct\"."
  }
}
